# PHP Music Application
This is a PHP-based web application for managing and playing music. It allows users to upload, view, and listen to music tracks.

# Prerequisites
Before running the application, make sure you have the following installed:

# Apache Web Server
# PHP (version 7.0 or higher)
# MySQL or MariaDB
# Installation

Clone the repository or download the source code.
Create a new MySQL database and import the mgs_db.sql file located in the database directory.
Rename the config.php.sample file to config.php and update the database credentials.
Move the entire project directory to your web server's document root (e.g., /var/www/html/).
Make sure the uploads directory is writable by the web server.
Access the application in your web browser using the appropriate URL (e.g., http://localhost/php-music-app).
Usage
Log in to the admin panel using the default credentials (username: admin, password: password).
Navigate to the "Musics" section to add, edit, or delete music tracks.
Upload music banners and audio files for each track.
Manage user accounts and permissions (if applicable).
Users can browse and listen to the available music tracks.
Bash Script
The deploy.sh bash script is provided to automate the deployment process. Here's how to use it:

# Navigate to the project directory
cd /path/to/php-music-app

# Run the deployment script
./deploy.sh



# The script will perform the following tasks:

Check if Apache and MySQL are installed.
Create a new MySQL database and import the mgs_db.sql file.
Copy the project files to the web server's document root.
Set the correct file permissions for the uploads directory.
Restart the Apache web server.
Note: Make sure to review and modify the script according to your specific requirements and server configuration.

